vectorData.altText: 7. Lesions of upper motor neurons in the spinal cord _____________ have ipsilateral effects.
That's right!  Lesions of upper motor neurons in the spinal cord, i.e. the LCST, always have ipsilateral effects because this tract decussates at the spinomedullary junction.
